# Introduction

Your code has problems with implementing Swing as well as being one main method.

Oracle has a helpful tutorial, [Creating a GUI With Swing](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/index.html).  Skip the Learning Swing with the NetBeans IDE section.  

Let&#39;s take this step by step.

# Step 1

The first thing I did was rename your main GUI class to something more meaningful, remove the player code, and focus on the GUI.  

I added a call to the `SwingUtilities` `invokeLater` method.  This method ensures that the Swing components are created and executed on the [Event Dispatch Thread][1].

Here&#39;s the result of that step.

